                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>THOMAS LARKE. I live in Union-place. On the 14th of July, between eleven and twelve o'clock at night, I was going home with Thomas Dean, my landlord - the prisoner ran up against me, and said, "I beg your pardon, Sir;" and as he said that, he drew my watch out of my pocket. I caught it with my left hand, and caught him with my right hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-210-person1870">
                  THOMAS 
                  DEAN
               <interp inst="t18270913-210-person1870" type="surname" value="DEAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-210-person1870" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-210-person1870" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Larke; his account is correct; I was about six feet before him; he called me; I turned, and saw the prisoner in his hands; he gave me the watch; I took it to the office - Larke was sober.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going along - this gentleman was in a mob, and seemed in liquor; he took me, and said I had robbed him; he took the watch from his pocket, and gave it to the other witness.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-210-verdict1185" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270913-210-verdict1185" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
               <p>
